<paragraph blockId="22.[163,778,909,1023]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis box="[163,283,910,931]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Third maxilliped ischium smooth, lacking vertical sulcus; epibranchial tooth small, pointed; postfrontal crest distinct, completely traversing carapace.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[163,779,1064,1208]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis box="[163,289,1064,1085]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Etymology:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels, 2022" authorityName="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels" authorityYear="2022" box="[301,438,1064,1086]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" status="TRIBE NOV." tribe="Erimetopini">Erimetopini</taxonomicName>
is derived from a combination of the English words 
<collectingCountry box="[413,485,1095,1116]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Congo</collectingCountry>
and West, as a reference to the range of this tribe that includes an area that encompasses the 
<collectingCountry box="[368,440,1156,1177]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Congo</collectingCountry>
Basin and all of West Africa (
<figureCitation box="[171,252,1186,1208]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="17.[145,224,1267,1289]" captionTargetBox="[225,1345,195,1227]" captionTargetId="figure-288@17.[225,1345,195,1227]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 8. Maps showing the distributional ranges of (A) Potamonautinae, (B) Maritimonautini, (C) Erimetopini and (D) Potamonautini." pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
). The gender is masculine.
</paragraph>
